    "summary": "As a researcher, my primary interest is the modern history of Jewish communities in the Islamic world and their responses to modernity. From a methodological standpoint I consider myself a historian, and as such the majority of my research is based on archival material and historic press in English, French, Arabic, and Hebrew, dating from the nineteenth and first half of the twentieth century. My current research rethinks the connection between transnational solidarity organizations and empire. The focus is on the centrality and agency of non-European elites, thereby challenging assumptions about the center and the periphery within colonial networks\n\nI have a passion for modern history and digital humanities, as represented by my former roles as the digital curator for the Jewish Historical Museum in Amsterdam and as the project lead for the openjournals.nl platform at the KNAW. Combined with eight years of experience in academic publishing, honing my skills in project development and management, I have a unique skill set and professional perspective for working with institutions looking to make culture accessible to all.\n\n\u2022\tDigital Curation\n\u2022      Project management \n\u2022\tDeveloping, organizing and publishing academic print and online content\n\u2022\tDeveloping online platforms for academic reference works and bibliographic databases\n\u2022\tInternational network of academics, librarians, and publishers\n\u2022\tOrganizing academic conferences & meetings\n\u2022\tFinancial development & management \n\u2022\tTeam management",
